President Trump held a meeting at the White House with citizens whose lives have been saved by law enforcement. He expressed his gratitude for the work of law enforcement officers and criticized the treatment they have received in recent weeks. He also discussed the increase in violent crime in some Democrat-run cities and accused radical politicians of waging war on innocent Americans. The President and other speakers at the meeting highlighted individual stories of police officers saving lives and emphasized the importance of supporting law enforcement. The President also addressed questions about the pardon of Michael Flynn and the reopening of schools amid the COVID-19 pandemic.